By Boxing Day, the building was still on lockdown, with residents on the West 20th Street side told to find somewhere else to spend the rest of the festive period while builders worked to repair the damaged wall.

No one was injured, but the building was evacuated, the fire department said.

The evacuation was ordered as a 
precaution after officials saw some small cracks in the wall where the 
facade fell, Fire Chief Tom McCarthy told reporters.

